   "source": [
    "# 09 โ Text Normalization\n",
    "**Goal:** Reducir la variaciรณn morfolรณgica del texto para que `correr`, `corriรณ`, `corriendo` traten al mismo concepto.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Stemming      โ cortar sufijos con reglas heurรญsticas  (rรกpido, ruidoso)\n",
    "Lemmatizaciรณn โ forma canรณnica lingรผรญsticamente correcta (lento, preciso, requiere diccionario)\n",
    "Char n-gramas โ fragmentos de caracteres โ robusto ante errores ortogrรกficos\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Sin NLTK ni spaCy: implementaremos las reglas de Snowball para espaรฑol."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "setup",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "os.chdir('/Volumes/SSD_Gabo/proyectos/growth-analytics')\n",
    "\n",
    "import re\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from collections import Counter\n",
    "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({\n",
    "    'figure.dpi': 130, 'axes.spines.top': False, 'axes.spines.right': False,\n",
    "    'axes.grid': True, 'grid.color': '#e8e8e8', 'axes.axisbelow': True,\n",
    "})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. El problema de la variaciรณn morfolรณgica"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Sin normalizaciรณn, estas palabras son features distintas\n",
    "variantes = {\n",
    "    'activar':      ['activ', 'activa', 'activar', 'activรณ', 'activando', 'activaciรณn', 'activaciones'],\n",
    "    'tarjeta':      ['tarjeta', 'tarjetas'],\n",
    "    'aprobar':      ['aprueba', 'aprobaron', 'aprobado', 'aprobaciรณn', 'aprobรณ'],\n",
    "    'lento/lenta':  ['lento', 'lenta', 'lentรญsimo', 'lentรญsima', 'lentamente'],\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "for base, variants in variantes.items():\n",
    "    print(f'{base:15s} โ {variants}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Stemmer de Snowball para espaรฑol (implementaciรณn simplificada)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class SpanishStemmer:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Stemmer heurรญstico para espaรฑol basado en el algoritmo Snowball.\n",
    "    Referencia: Snowball (Porter 2002) โ https://snowballstem.org/algorithms/spanish/\n",
    "    Implementaciรณn simplificada para uso educativo.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    VOWELS = set('aeiouรกรฉรญรณรบรผ')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Sufijos ordenados de mรกs largo a mรกs corto\n",
    "    SUFFIXES = [\n",
    "        # verbales\n",
    "        'aciones', 'izaciรณn', 'izando', 'izaciรณn',\n",
    "        'amiento', 'amiento',\n",
    "        'aciones', 'amiento',\n",
    "        'iendo', 'ando', 'aron', 'aron', 'aban',\n",
    "        'ciรณn', 'siรณn', 'ciรณn',\n",
    "        'ados', 'idas', 'ados',\n",
    "        'ado', 'ida', 'ado',\n",
    "        'ando', 'ando',\n",
    "        'aron', 'aron',\n",
    "        'aban', 'aban',\n",
    "        'mente',\n",
    "        # nominales\n",
    "        'รญsimo', 'รญsima',\n",
    "        'iones', 'ciรณn',\n",
    "        'ando', 'iendo',\n",
    "        'aron', 'aban',\n",
    "        'ado', 'ada', 'ido', 'ida',\n",
    "        'ando', 'iente',\n",
    "        'mente',\n",
    "        # plurales y gรฉneros\n",
    "        'iones', 'ciรณn',\n",
    "        'es', 'as', 'os',\n",
    "        'รณ', 'รณ',\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Eliminar diacrรญticos\n",
    "    _ACCENTS = str.maketrans('รกรฉรญรณรบ', 'aeiou')\n",
    "\n",
    "    def stem(self, word):\n",
    "        word = word.lower().translate(self._ACCENTS)\n",
    "        if len(word) <= 4:\n",
    "            return word\n",
    "        for suffix in sorted(set(self.SUFFIXES), key=len, reverse=True):\n",
    "            if word.endswith(suffix) and len(word) - len(suffix) >= 3:\n",
    "                return word[:-len(suffix)]\n",
    "        # eliminar plural simple\n",
    "        if word.endswith('es') and len(word) > 5:\n",
    "            return word[:-2]\n",
    "        if word.endswith('s') and len(word) > 4 and word[-2] not in self.VOWELS:\n",
    "            return word[:-1]\n",
    "        return word\n",
    "\n",
    "stemmer = SpanishStemmer()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Demostraciรณn\n",
    "for base, variants in variantes.items():\n",
    "    stems = [stemmer.stem(v) for v in variants]\n",
    "    unique_stems = set(stems)\n",
    "    print(f'{base:15s} โ stems: {stems}')\n",
    "    print(f'{\"\":15s}   รบnicos: {unique_stems}\\n')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Integrar el stemmer con sklearn como preprocessor\n",
    "def make_stem_preprocessor(stemmer):\n",
    "    def preprocess_stem(text):\n",
    "        text = text.lower()\n",
    "        text = re.sub(r'[^\\wรกรฉรญรณรบรผรฑ\\s]', ' ', text)\n",
    "        text = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text).strip()\n",
    "        tokens = text.split()\n",
    "        return ' '.join(stemmer.stem(t) for t in tokens)\n",
    "    return preprocess_stem\n",
    "\n",
    "preprocess_stem = make_stem_preprocessor(stemmer)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ejemplo\n",
    "text = 'La activaciรณn de mi tarjeta fue muy lenta, tardรฉ horas activรกndola'\n",
    "print('Original:', text)\n",
    "print('Stemmed: ', preprocess_stem(text))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Lemmatizaciรณn simple con diccionario"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Lemmatizador basado en diccionario para dominio fintech\n",
    "# En producciรณn: spaCy es_core_news_sm o stanza\n",
    "LEMMA_DICT = {\n",
    "    # verbos\n",
    "    'activรณ': 'activar', 'activando': 'activar', 'activaciรณn': 'activar',\n",
    "    'activaciones': 'activar', 'activa': 'activar', 'activado': 'activar',\n",
    "    'aprobaron': 'aprobar', 'aprobado': 'aprobar', 'aprobaciรณn': 'aprobar',\n",
    "    'aprueba': 'aprobar',\n",
    "    'falla': 'fallar', 'fallรณ': 'fallar', 'fallando': 'fallar',\n",
    "    'cargando': 'cargar', 'cargรณ': 'cargar', 'carga': 'cargar',\n",
    "    'llegรณ': 'llegar', 'llegando': 'llegar',\n",
    "    'tardรฉ': 'tardar', 'tarda': 'tardar', 'tardando': 'tardar',\n",
    "    'resolvieron': 'resolver', 'resuelven': 'resolver',\n",
    "    # adjetivos\n",
    "    'lenta': 'lento', 'lentas': 'lento', 'lentos': 'lento',\n",
    "    'lentรญsima': 'lento', 'lentรญsimo': 'lento',\n",
    "    'rรกpida': 'rรกpido', 'rรกpidas': 'rรกpido', 'rรกpidamente': 'rรกpido',\n",
    "    # sustantivos\n",
    "    'tarjetas': 'tarjeta', 'documentos': 'documento',\n",
    "    'beneficios': 'beneficio', 'problemas': 'problema',\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "def lemmatize(text):\n",
    "    text = text.lower()\n",
    "    text = re.sub(r'[^\\wรกรฉรญรณรบรผรฑ\\s]', ' ', text)\n",
    "    text = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text).strip()\n",
    "    tokens = text.split()\n",
    "    return ' '.join(LEMMA_DICT.get(t, t) for t in tokens)\n",
    "\n",
    "examples = [\n",
    "    'La activaciรณn de mis tarjetas fue lentรญsima',\n",
    "    'Aprobaron mi solicitud rรกpidamente',\n",
    "    'La app falla cargando los documentos',\n",
    "]\n",
    "for e in examples:\n",
    "    print(f'Original:   {e}')\n",
    "    print(f'Lematizado: {lemmatize(e)}\\n')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Character n-grams โ robusto ante errores ortogrรกficos"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Char n-grams capturan morfologรญa y son robustos ante typos\n",
    "def char_ngrams(text, n=3):\n",
    "    text = text.replace(' ', '_')  # marcar espacios\n",
    "    return [text[i:i+n] for i in range(len(text) - n + 1)]\n",
    "\n",
    "word1 = 'activaciรณn'\n",
    "word2 = 'activasion'  # typo\n",
    "\n",
    "ng1 = set(char_ngrams(word1, 3))\n",
    "ng2 = set(char_ngrams(word2, 3))\n",
    "overlap = ng1 & ng2\n",
    "jaccard = len(overlap) / len(ng1 | ng2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Trigramas de \"{word1}\": {sorted(ng1)}')\n",
    "print(f'Trigramas de \"{word2}\": {sorted(ng2)}')\n",
    "print(f'En comรบn: {sorted(overlap)}')\n",
    "print(f'Similitud Jaccard (robusta al typo): {jaccard:.3f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# TfidfVectorizer con char n-grams\n",
    "tfidf_char = TfidfVectorizer(\n",
    "    analyzer='char_wb',    # char n-grams delimitados por espacios\n",
    "    ngram_range=(3, 5),    # trigramas a pentagramas de caracteres\n",
    "    min_df=2,\n",
    "    sublinear_tf=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "docs_with_typos = [\n",
    "    'La activasion de mi tarjeta fue lenta',   # typo: activasion\n",
    "    'La activaciรณn de mi tarjeta fue lenta',   # correcto\n",
    "    'La app fala constantemente',              # typo: fala\n",
    "    'La app falla constantemente',             # correcto\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "X_char = tfidf_char.fit_transform(docs_with_typos)\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\n",
    "sim = cosine_similarity(X_char)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Similitud con char n-grams (robusta a typos):')\n",
    "print(f'  \"activasion\" vs \"activaciรณn\": {sim[0,1]:.3f}')\n",
    "print(f'  \"fala\" vs \"falla\":            {sim[2,3]:.3f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Comparaciรณn โ BoW vs Stemming vs Char n-grams"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Dataset de feedback\n",
    "rng = np.random.default_rng(42)\n",
    "templates_pos = [\n",
    "    'El proceso de solicitud fue muy rรกpido y eficiente',\n",
    "    'Excelente servicio, aprobaron mi tarjeta rรกpidamente',\n",
    "    'La app funciona perfecto, muy fรกcil de usar',\n",
    "    'Increรญbles beneficios, recomiendo la tarjeta',\n",
    "    'Atenciรณn al cliente excepcional, resolvieron todo',\n",
    "    'Proceso de activaciรณn muy sencillo y sin problemas',\n",
    "]\n",
    "templates_neg = [\n",
    "    'La app estรก muy lenta, tardรฉ mucho en activar la tarjeta',\n",
    "    'No me llegรณ el OTP, tuve que llamar varias veces',\n",
    "    'La carga de documentos falla constantemente',\n",
    "    'Llevo dรญas esperando la evaluaciรณn crediticia',\n",
    "    'El call center no responde, pรฉsimo servicio',\n",
    "    'El proceso de aprobaciรณn es muy lento e ineficiente',\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "pos = [templates_pos[rng.integers(6)] for _ in range(300)]\n",
    "neg = [templates_neg[rng.integers(6)] for _ in range(300)]\n",
    "X_texts = pos + neg\n",
    "y = np.array([1]*300 + [0]*300)\n",
    "\n",
    "STOPWORDS_ES = [\n",
    "    'a','al','como','con','de','del','el','en','es','la','las','lo','los',\n",
    "    'me','mi','muy','no','o','para','por','que','se','si','sin','su','te',\n",
    "    'todo','un','una','y','yo',\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "def preprocess_base(text):\n",
    "    text = text.lower()\n",
    "    text = re.sub(r'[^\\wรกรฉรญรณรบรผรฑ\\s]', ' ', text)\n",
    "    return re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text).strip()\n",
    "\n",
    "configs = [\n",
    "    ('BoW (palabras)',        TfidfVectorizer(preprocessor=preprocess_base, stop_words=STOPWORDS_ES, ngram_range=(1,2))),\n",
    "    ('Stemming',             TfidfVectorizer(preprocessor=preprocess_stem, stop_words=STOPWORDS_ES, ngram_range=(1,2))),\n",
    "    ('Lemmatizaciรณn',        TfidfVectorizer(preprocessor=lemmatize,        stop_words=STOPWORDS_ES, ngram_range=(1,2))),\n",
    "    ('Char n-grams (3-5)',   TfidfVectorizer(analyzer='char_wb', ngram_range=(3,5), min_df=2)),\n",
    "    ('Word + Char (ensemble)', None),   # combinaciรณn\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'{\"Config\":<28} {\"F1 CV (5-fold)\":>15}')\n",
    "print('-' * 45)\n",
    "\n",
    "for name, vec in configs[:-1]:\n",
    "    pipe = Pipeline([('vec', vec), ('clf', LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000))])\n",
    "    f1 = cross_val_score(pipe, X_texts, y, cv=5, scoring='f1').mean()\n",
    "    print(f'{name:<28} {f1:.4f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ensemble: concatenar features de word y char\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import FeatureUnion\n",
    "ensemble = Pipeline([\n",
    "    ('features', FeatureUnion([\n",
    "        ('word', TfidfVectorizer(preprocessor=preprocess_stem, stop_words=STOPWORDS_ES, ngram_range=(1,2))),\n",
    "        ('char', TfidfVectorizer(analyzer='char_wb', ngram_range=(3,5), min_df=2)),\n",
    "    ])),\n",
    "    ('clf', LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000)),\n",
    "])\n",
    "f1_ens = cross_val_score(ensemble, X_texts, y, cv=5, scoring='f1').mean()\n",
    "print(f'{\"Word + Char (ensemble)\":<28} {f1_ens:.4f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-summary",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Resumen\n",
    "| Tรฉcnica | Ventaja | Desventaja |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Sin normalizaciรณn | Simple | Variantes morfolรณgicas = features distintas |\n",
    "| Stemming | Rรกpido, sin recursos externos | Cortes bruscos, puede dar raรญces incorrectas |\n",
    "| Lemmatizaciรณn | Lingรผรญsticamente correcta | Necesita diccionario o modelo |\n",
    "| Char n-grams | Robusto a typos, captura morfologรญa | Vocabulario enorme, mรกs lento |\n",
    "| Ensemble word+char | Mejor de ambos mundos | Mayor costo computacional |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Siguiente:** `10_clustering.ipynb` โ agrupar documentos sin etiquetas."
   ]
  }
